The course gives an overview of the basics of counselling, opportunities to apply counselling in social work and rehabilitation, practical acquisition of basic techniques for primary counselling.
Topics: 
Process and basic principles of counselling. Personality and professional skills of the counsellor. Professional ethics of a counsellor. Factors influencing counselling process. Basic counselling theories (basic concepts, key concepts, basic techniques). Basic counselling techniques applied in social work (active listening).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is designed to develop a conceptual understanding of using counselling in social work and rehabilitation and shape core counselling skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) understands basic principles of counselling; 2) knows counselling application areas; 3) is familiar with the process of counselling; 4) is aware of the limits of counselling intervention (incl ethical aspects); 5) is aware of client-centered approach in counselling; 6) is familiar with common counselling theories; 7) is able to identify and analyze the factors affecting the process of counselling; 8) has active listening skills; 9) is able to support client activity at different stages of the counselling process; 10) understands the importance of the process of self-reflection in the professional setting; 11) knows modern professional vocabulary in English and Estonian.
